Author: jspook16#3059
Content: I guess i never heard of it yet. (a bit off topic, but does komodo prevent someone from creating an asset chain with the same name as an existing chain?)

Author: blackjok3r#3181
Content: no

Author: blackjok3r#3181
Content: If the supply is diffrent, and it uses diff params it wont "find" the other chain at any time.

Author: jspook16#3059
Content: @blackjok3r could that be problem?

Author: Alright#0419
Content: if you change any of the ac_ parameters, it changes the coin's magic value

Author: Alright#0419
Content: magic value being what determines the ports it uses

Author: Alright#0419
Content: so `-ac_name=DEX -ac_supply=999999` and `-ac_name=DEX -ac_supply=1000000` would be two completely different coins and their nodes would never interact

Author: jspook16#3059
Content: ok just curious about that. what about the faucetget.....does it work like my comment above?

Author: Alright#0419
Content: `faucetget` will output a raw tx that is spending a CC vout from the contract and sending part of it to yourself

Author: Alright#0419
Content: you then broadcast it

Author: Alright#0419
Content: That's the basis for a lot of the contracts. There are coins in a contract address with the special vout type "CryptoCondition". Anyone can spend them, but these spends must fit the rules laid out by the contract
